<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1946-07-17T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1946-07-17T00:00:00-05:00" n="1070" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1070">
                    <note rend="inline" type="source">893.516/6–1446</note>
                    <head>
                        <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to Mr.
                                <persName type="to">Thomas W. Lamont</persName>, of New York</hi>
                    </head>
                    <opener>
                        <dateline rendition="#right">
                            <placeName>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1946-07-17">July 17,
                            1946</date>.</dateline>
                    </opener>
                    <p>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">My Dear Mr. Lamont</hi>: I acknowledge with
                        appreciation your letter of June 14, 1946 with enclosures, informing this
                        Department of recent correspondence with the Honkgong and Shanghai Banking
                        Corporation regarding steps to be taken towards termination of the China
                        Consortium. The Department would be interested to learn of the action taken
                        with reference to final dissolution of the Consortium, and of the procedure
                        adopted for notifying the Chinese Government.</p>
                    <p>Sincerely yours,</p>
                    <closer>For the Secretary of State: <lb/>
                        <signed>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">William</hi> L. <hi rend="smallcaps">Clayton</hi>
                        </signed>
                        <lb/>
                        <hi rend="italic">Assistant Secretary</hi>
                    </closer>
                </div>
                </body></text></TEI>